This paper is primarily focused on information theory and coding, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of decoding algorithms, which could also place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The use of heuristics and tree search strategies suggests a potential fit with the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category, while the discussion of error correction performance could also place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
